[Human infection with Trypanosoma cruzi is well known in Argentina. A new study used molecular epidemiology to describe the distribution of different genotypes in 239 patients (Cura CI et al. Trypanosoma cruzi Discrete Typing Units in Chagas disease patients from endemic and non-endemic regions of Argentina. Parasitology. 2012 Feb 6:1-6. [Epub ahead of print].

A study of Chagas disease in pregnant women of South American origin living in Spain found that 5.3 percent of women emigrating from Argentina to Spain had specific-atibodies against T. cruzi, emphasizing that the infection is widespread in Argentina. HealthMap location: http://healthmap.org/r/1MhD - Mod. EP]
